# Why Bronze Exists

Bronze is your **system of record**.

Think of it as:

```text id="6g7vra"
What exactly arrived from the source?
```

If someone asks:

> "Can you prove what Kafka sent yesterday at 2 PM?"

You should be able to go back to Bronze and see the original event.

---

# Wrong Approach

```text id="t2v5ut"
Kafka
 ↓
Spark
 ↓
Bronze (remove duplicates)
```

Problem:

You've already modified the raw data.

Now you can never answer:

```text id="f9h7e1"
What actually arrived?
```

Auditability is lost.

---

# Correct Approach

```text id="rrk9qj"
Kafka
 ↓
Spark
 ↓
Bronze (raw)
 ↓
Silver (cleaned)
```

Bronze stores:

```json id="1uz8wq"
Order 1001
Order 1001
```

Silver stores:

```json id="t9k0qa"
Order 1001
```

One clean version.

